Motorists using Ngong Road will have to find alternative routes as sections of the road will be closed for construction. The Kenya Urban Roads Authority has announced that the section between Faulu Bank, Garage, Water Company, and Baptist Church access will be closed today. ALSO READ: To prosper, cities must do away with archaic, rigid processes The Mucai Drive, Residence, and Carmax access will be shut on Friday. The China Centre to Shell access will be closed on Saturday. The closure will be for 24 hours to lay asphalt surface.